snippet.textDisplay: After watching this video, it's time for me to register my opinion. I've never thought burnout competitions were very interesting. Taking a high-powered car and doing donuts doesn't do much for me. Drifting, however, requires some skill to keep the tires spinning and the car sliding while negotiating a turn. A few professional drifters (like Vaughn Gitten) have demonstrated some skillful work in their videos. Your layout at the Freedom Factory seems like a perfect place for drifters. Admittedly, I've never done either so I can't say which would be more fun from a driver's perspective -- I'm speaking from the standpoint of a spectator.
